qas.question: Which invention resulted in more widespread use of the printed word?
In what year did Constantinople fall?
In what year did Vasco da Gama sail around India and Africa?
In what year was Columbus' expedition to the Americas?
The Protestant Reformation is attributed to what two developments that resulted from the invention of printing?

answers.text: dissemination of the printed word and democratized learning

qas.question: Which invention resulted in less widespread use of the printed word?
In what year did Constantinople rise?
In what year did Vasco da Gama sail through India and Africa?
In what year was Columbus' expedition to the Africas?

plausible_answers.text: dissemination of the printed word and democratized learning

qas.question: The Protestant Reformation isn't attributed to what two developments that resulted from the invention of printing?

context: Combined with this influx of classical ideas was the invention of <a0_0><b5_0>printing<b5_0/><a0_0/> which facilitated <a4_0><b9_0>dissemination of the printed word and democratized learning<b9_0/><a4_0/>. These two things would later lead to the Protestant Reformation. Toward the end of the period, an era of discovery began (Age of Discovery). The rise of the Ottoman Empire, culminating in the Fall of Constantinople in <a1_0><b6_0>1453<b6_0/><a1_0/>, eroded the last remnants of the Byzantine Empire and cut off trading possibilities with the east. Europeans were forced to seek new trading routes, leading to the expedition of Columbus to the Americas in <a3_0><b8_0>1492<b8_0/><a3_0/>, and Vasco da Gama’s circumnavigation of India and Africa in <a2_0><b7_0>1498<b7_0/><a2_0/>. Their discoveries strengthened the economy and power of European nations.
